events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-13 Brentford vs Arsenal
events.strDescriptionEN: Premier League newcomer Brentford plays its first-ever game in the division against Arsenal with the Gunners keen to start off on a positive note, after finishing last season 8th and missing out on European soccer for the first time since 1996.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Burnley vs Brighton
events.strDescriptionEN: After finishing 17th and 16th last season respectively, both Burnley and Brighton and Hove Albion will both be aiming to push on in the new campaign. They begin their seasons at Turf Moor, where last season they shared the points in a 1-1 draw.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Chelsea vs Crystal Palace
events.strDescriptionEN: Last seasons UEFA Champions League winner Chelsea welcomes Crystal Palace to Stamford Bridge on the opening day of the new campaign. The Eagles last won here in April 2017 but have now lost seven straight games against the Blues.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Everton vs Southampton
events.strDescriptionEN: After Carlo Ancelottis shock return to Real Madrid, Everton begins yet another season under new guidance. The Toffees home form was poor last season, can Southampton capitalize to win a league game at Goodison Park for the first time since 1997?

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Leicester vs Wolves
events.strDescriptionEN: Leicester City returns to King Power Stadium for the first time since its loss to Tottenham Hotspur last season which saw it miss out on UEFA Champions League soccer. Its opponent, Wolverhampton Wanderers, starts a new era under Bruno Lage.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Manchester United vs Leeds
events.strDescriptionEN: Fierce rivals Manchester United and Leeds United clash in the most eye-watering tie of the opening weekend. It was an eight-goal thriller when they met at Old Trafford last year with United winning 6-2, but Leeds held it to a goalless draw in April.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Norwich vs Liverpool
events.strDescriptionEN: Two years after opening its last Premier League campaign at Anfield, Norwich City hosts Liverpool ahead of a challenging run of fixtures. The Reds are 14 games unbeaten against the Canaries and have not lost an opening day fixture since 2012.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Watford vs Aston Villa
events.strDescriptionEN: Vicarage Road is yet again a Premier League destination as Aston Villa visit Watford on the opening weekend. Troy Deeney and Ismaila Sarr wrapped up a 3-0 victory for the Hornets in the last meeting in Hertfordshire back in 2019.

English Premier League 2021-10-16 Aston Villa vs Wolves
events.strDescriptionEN: Aston Villa hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Villa Park. The last three meetings have only seen two goals in total - which is the same as the number of red cards, with each team getting one in the same game.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Brentford vs Chelsea
English Premier League 2021-10-16 Leicester vs Manchester United
events.strDescriptionEN: Leicester City hosts Manchester United at King Power Stadium. The Red Devils have lost two successive games against Leicester in the FA Cup final and Premier League respectively, and look to exact its revenge against The Foxes this time out.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Manchester City vs Burnley
events.strDescriptionEN: Reigning champion Manchester City hosts Sean Dyches Burnley at Etihad Stadium. City boasts an excellent record against its opponent, having conceded only two league goals to Burnley since 2018.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Norwich vs Brighton
events.strDescriptionEN: Newly-promoted Norwich City clashes with Brighton and Hove Albion at Carrow Road. Both sides will be vying for a hugely important win, as they bid to extend their stay in the Premier League by another year.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Southampton vs Leeds
events.strDescriptionEN: Southampton lines up against Leeds United at St Mary’s Stadium. Southampton has not recorded a triumph over Leeds since March 2012, which came in the form of a narrow 1-0 victory in England’s second division.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Watford vs Liverpool
events.strDescriptionEN: Liverpool travels to Vicarage Road, where it faces newly promoted Watford in the Premier League. The Hornets sacked Xisco Munoz after a defeat to Leeds United, and Claudio Ranieri will be the man in charge against the Reds.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-17 Everton vs West Ham
English Premier League 2021-10-17 Newcastle vs Tottenham
English Premier League 2021-10-18 Arsenal vs Crystal Palace
English Premier League 2021-10-22 Arsenal vs Aston Villa
events.strDescriptionEN: Mikel Artetas Arsenal welcomes Aston Villa to Emirates Stadium. The Gunners last tasted victory against its opponents in 2019, with Villa having won the last three consecutive games between the sides, including a 3-0 triumph in north London.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Brighton vs Manchester City
events.strDescriptionEN: Pep Guardiola’s Manchester City travels to Amex Stadium, where Brighton and Hove Albion lay in wait. The champions will be out to avenge its shock defeat to the Seagulls last season, where a 2-0 lead was surrendered during a stunning 3-2 loss.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Chelsea vs Norwich
events.strDescriptionEN: Chelsea welcomes newly promoted Norwich City to Stamford Bridge for a Premier League showdown. The Canaries have not tasted victory over the Blues since 1994, and will be keen to stage a big upset in London.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Crystal Palace vs Newcastle
events.strDescriptionEN: Patrick Vieira’s Crystal Palace host Newcastle United in the Premier League at Selhurst Park. The Magpies were beaten by Tottenham Hotspur in the first game since the clubs takeover. Can they turn things around against the Eagles?

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Everton vs Watford
events.strDescriptionEN: Watford pays a visit to Goodison Park, where it faces Everton in the Premier League. Claudio Ranieris time in charge of Watford started with a mauling by Liverpool. Will it be another sobering experience against a team from Merseyside?

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Leeds vs Wolves
events.strDescriptionEN: All the action as Leeds United hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Elland Road. Marcelo Bielsas Leeds is hovering above the Premier League relegation zone after a loss to Southampton, while Wolves beat Aston Villa in thrilling style last time out.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Southampton vs Burnley
events.strDescriptionEN: Southampton welcomes Sean Dyches Burnley to St Mary’s Stadium. With both teams rooted firmly in the bottom half of the Premier League table, neither will be wanting to settle for anything less than three points.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-24 Brentford vs Leicester
events.strDescriptionEN: All the action as Brentford hosts Leicester City in the Premier League. The away side travels to London looking to build on a win over Manchester United, while the Bees look to bounce back from a narrow home defeat to Chelsea.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-24 Manchester United vs Liverpool
events.strDescriptionEN: Two of Englands biggest teams go head-to-head as Manchester United hosts Liverpool. With the likes of Jadon Sancho and Cristiano Ronaldo to call upon, United will hope for a first win over the Reds in the Premier League since 2018.

events.strFilename: English Premier League 2021-10-24 West Ham vs Tottenham
events.strDescriptionEN: West Ham United hosts Tottenham Hotspur in a London derby. Nuno Espirito Santo’s Spurs side travels to London Stadium with Harry Kane looking to build on his first Premier League goal of the season against Newcastle United last weekend.
